The paper deals with the construction of contour trees, which is a fundamental data structure in computational geometry and topology. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents a refined time complexity that depends on the contour tree structure, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of contour trees in data analysis and visualization, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) or cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper discusses lower bounds, which could place it in cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Formal Verification).
